9, 1885). Supplements accompany many issues. Volume I, Number 1 (September 4, 1880); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 23, 2021). Volume 5, Number 52 = whole number 261 (August 29, 1885) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Feb. 23, 2021). Daily Honolulu press 2767-276X (DLC) 2021220159 (OCoLC)904427830"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:13.555Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220158/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["online resource", "2767-2786", "2021220158", "2021220159", "701514961", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "saturday press (honolulu, h.i.) 1880-1885 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Saturday press", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220158/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1882", "dates": ["[1882 TO 1895]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Print began with No. 1 (Feb. 1, 1882); print ceased with Vol. IX, No. 1337 [i.e. 1340] (May 15, 1895). Issues for 1882-Dec. 19, 1891 called also v. 1-15; Dec. 21, 1891-1895, called v. 2-9. Has semimonthly supplements, 1888, called: Daily bulletin summary; has weekly supplements, 1889-May 15, 1895, called: Weekly bulletin summary (varies). No. 1 (February 1, 1882); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Vol. IX, No. 1337 [i.e. 1340] (May 15, 1895) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Evening bulletin (Honolulu, Hawaii) 2767-8628 (DLC) 2021220227 (OCoLC)904430143"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:12.813Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["2021220226", "online resource", "2021220227", "2767-8636", "701512295", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["J.W. Robertson's daily bulletin"], "partof": ["directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the daily bulletin (honolulu [hawaii]) 1882-1895 [online resource]", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD Internet Access AEU", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "periodicals", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "The Daily bulletin", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220226/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1895", "dates": ["[1895 TO 1912]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sunday) Print began with Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 16, 1895); ceased with No. 5,276 (June 29, 1912). Issued also on Sunday, Jan. 26-Apr. 1902, as: Sunday bulletin. Editors: June 17, 1895-June 10, 1898, D. Logan; June 13, 1898-1912, W.R. Farrington. Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 16, 1895); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). No. 5,267 (June 29, 1912) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Mar. 24, 2021). Hawaiian star 2771-0688 (DLC) 2021220559 (OCoLC)904431854 Honolulu star-bulletin (Online) 2326-1145 (DLC) 2013218511 (OCoLC)232117605"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["honolulu", "united states", "hawaii"], "number": ["2021220226", "online resource", "2021220227", "2021220559", "2021220228", "904430143", "2767-8628", "2013218511", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Sunday bulletin"], "partof": ["evening bulletin (honolulu [oahu, hawaii]) 1895-1912 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 32.179367, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "periodicals", "hawaii", "honolulu (hawaii)", "honolulu", "electronic journals", "united states"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T21:01:49.831Z", "title": "Evening bulletin", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2021220227/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220249/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["kenyon, g. c.", "sheldon, j. g. m. (john g. m.)", "spencer, thomas p."], "date": "1891", "dates": ["[1891 TO 1895]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sat.-Sun.) Print began in May 1891; ceased in 1895. Editors: T.P. Spencer, G.C. Kenyon, J.G.M. Sheldon. Cf. Mookini, E.K. Hawaiian newspapers. Beginning with Feb. 1, 1894 issue, vol. numbering repeats from buke 1, helu 1. In Hawaiian. Issued simultaneously with daily bilingual (Hawaiian/English) ed. of the same title: Hawaii holomua. Vol. III, No. 143 (June 20, 1894); title from caption (Chronicling America's website, viewed Apr. 5, 2021). Vol. III, No. 176 (July 30, 1894) (Chronicling America's website, viewed Apr. 5, 2021)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2021220249/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "l